Mask Up and Celebrate the Fourth Safely

The St. Louis County Department of Public has masks available for anyone in need, especially over the upcoming holiday weekend. If you are in need of a mask, drive by any of our clinic locations, John C. Murphy in Berkeley, South County Health Center in Sunset Hills, or our North Central Health Clinic in Pine Lawn. Mask pick is available today starting at 1PM until 5PM, and tomorrow from 8AM until 5PM. This is highly encouraged to keep our community safe.

South County Health Center
4580 South Lindbergh
Sunset Hills, MO 63128

post_text: Student choice went from the classroom to the lunch room today at Hancock High and Middle Schools. We held a taste test so students could choose a new item for the menu. The two choices....build your own flatbread pizza or build your own Bok Choy Chinese meal. The winner is---Bok Choy, which received 157 student votes. The flatbread pizza got 75 student votes. The new menu item begins tomorrow!

post_text: Great day of training for our students and staff!
shared_text:
Tier One Tactical Solutions
September 21, 2018 at 12:56 PM ·

Morning huddle. Big day today at Hancock Place School District. It’s the first district that has trained its kids Pre-K through 12th grade on active killer situations/tourniquet first aid. We teach stranger danger, earthquake, fire drills— (we have not had a fire death at a school since 1958) We truly believe you also need to have the kids trained, too, in this to make it all work. It’s all taught at age appropriate levels. We even have a mascot named Bill-E in honor of our 4E©️ program, who you’ll see later today at the elementary & pre-K. Hope you’ll follow us today on Facebook, Instagram & Insta Story to learn more about what it looks like. We think you’ll be surprised at the education the kids get without scaring them & the fun they have. Thank you to all the administrators, staff & teachers for ALL that you do every single day to keep our kids safe.
Follow us on Instagram at instagram.com/tieronetacticalsolutions
Follow us on Twitter @tieronestl

post_text:
Providing a safe and nurturing learning environment for Hancock Place students and staff is our highest priority. For the second consecutive year, Hancock Place District again will train in active intruder situations for our students, staff, and administration. For several years, the District has partnered with Tier One Tactical Solutions to develop and implement this program. Active intruder training is an important component of our safety plan and the Hancock Place School District has adopted options-based active intruder protocols for students and staff. This training will be conducted on Friday, September 21, 2018.

The focus of the day will be on actively practicing skills and teaching students options if faced with a crisis situation. These skills are applicable in school and anywhere students may encounter an active shooter situation. All school activities will be age appropriate for each group.

post_text:
The safety of our students is always a priority during winter weather. It's important for parents to have their students bundle up in layers and wear hats and gloves

Anytime the temperature or wind chill temperature reaches the point where exposed skin could experience frostbite, we consider closing school. Hancock Place uses the National Weather service wind chill chart as a guide when determining whether to close school or to reduce recess time.
